Nigerians have mocked Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo after he paid tribute to Lt. Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru, the late Chief of Army Staff, who died in a plane crash on Friday. Osinbajo and President Muhammadu Buhari were conspicuously missing at the funeral of the Army chief on Saturday, sparking outrage on social media. However, in a tweet on Sunday morning, Osinbajo paid tribute to Attahiru and the other late officers on the ill-fated plane. 🕊🕊🕊 May their memories remain ever blessed. pic.twitter.com/A09wFyBex9 — Prof Yemi Osinbajo (@ProfOsinbajo) May 23, 2021  Responding to his tweet, Nigerians slammed him for paying his tribute a day after the deceaseds were buried. “Their Blood is on the Hands of all of you in this government,” a Twitter user, John, said. “King of Condolences….,” wrote Akan CE. Another Twitter user, Femi, wrote: “Lmao wizkid plis.” “Tweet isn’t enough, not a remedy for your absence,” Longfellow said. “Useless man,” Prince of Africa wrote. “Your Administration Is Failed,” wireless_Jnr_5G_Network wrote. “Over raw best [sic] in twitter Vice President,” Dark Man X said. Attahiru: Names of officers with Army Chief in plane crash emerges 